raw_data.title: Administrative Support I
raw_data.description: Provides administrative support to the project. Supports the production of project deliverables and performs clerical and administrative functions required to complete work related to the project.

raw_data.title: Administrative Support II
raw_data.description: Provides administrative support to the project. Supports the production of project deliverables and performs clerical and administrative functions required to complete work related to the project. Supports contract execution, coordinates personnel, project quality, and schedule. Oversees aspects of projects including day-to-day management of overall contract support operations.

raw_data.title: Analyst I
raw_data.description: Possesses and applies expertise in one or more professional or technical specialty areas on multiple complex work assignments. Assignments are broad, requiring originality and innovation in determining how to accomplish tasks.  Operates with appreciable latitude in developing methodology and presenting solutions to problems. Applies management analysis processes, statistical methods, and advanced technical and analytical research techniques to determine solutions based on client requirements with an IT services/solutions-based scope.  Analyzes operational activities to obtain a quantitative, rational basis for decision making and resource allocation. Employs process improvements and reengineering methodologies and principles for modernization of systems and projects. Creates project plans to achieve performance-based objectives, enhancing implementation, systems and service.  Provides integral support in mission requirements determination, conceptualization, design, development, testing, verification and validation, documentation, and implementation of system applications.

raw_data.title: Analyst II
raw_data.description: Possesses and applies expert technical knowledge in multiple professional fields with direct responsibility for the completion of projects of major complexity and importance.  Recognized thought and strategy leader in professional and technical discipline.  Establishes goals, plans, and practices, and manages the technical development work on complex projects with the application of new and unique technologies.  Provides technical leadership and expert consultation to the client.  Operates independently with responsibility for major contract tasks and deliverables. Applies management analysis processes, statistical methods, and advanced technical and analytical research techniques to determine solutions based on client requirements with an IT services/solutions-based scope.  Analyzes operational activities to obtain a quantitative, rational basis for decision making and resource allocation. Employs process improvements and reengineering methodologies and principles for modernization of systems and projects. Creates project plans to achieve performance-based objectives, enhancing implementation, systems and service.  Provides integral support in mission requirements determination, conceptualization, design, development, testing, verification and validation, documentation, and implementation of system applications.  Analyst disciplines include but are not limited to mission analysis, requirements analysis and development, information assurance and security, telecommunications, performance standards and metrics, business process reengineering and change management, compliance and validation, configuration management, continuity planning and disaster recovery, COTS product evaluations, distance learning, training, economic business analysis, biometrics, identity protection and access management, instructional systems design, intelligence analysis, modeling and simulation, operations research, policy analysis and development, program and budget analysis, risk analysis and management, financial analysis, technical consulting and planning, and transformation and enterprise business strategy.

raw_data.title: Analyst III
raw_data.description: Manages mission-critical tasks across multiple functional areas.  Provides leadership for key tasks and resolves problems for major functional areas through assessment of complex and technically challenging situations.  Has domain and expert technical knowledge of functional areas and programmatic knowledge practice-wide.  Manages, controls, and directs the activities of multiple functional areas through program and project/task managers with overall responsibility for the implementation of project phases.  Is responsible for decision making that has long-term impact on meeting major project performance objectives. Applies management analysis processes, statistical methods, and advanced technical and analytical research techniques to determine solutions based on client requirements with an IT services/solutions-based scope.  Analyzes operational activities to obtain a quantitative, rational basis for decision making and resource allocation. Employs process improvements and reengineering methodologies and principles for modernization of systems and projects. Creates project plans to achieve performance-based objectives, enhancing implementation, systems and service.  Provides integral support in mission requirements determination, conceptualization, design, development, testing, verification and validation, documentation, and implementation of system applications.  Analyst disciplines include but are not limited to mission analysis, requirements analysis and development, information assurance and security, telecommunications, performance standards and metrics, business process reengineering and change management, compliance and validation, configuration management, continuity planning and disaster recovery, COTS product evaluations, distance learning, training, economic business analysis, biometrics, identity protection and access management, instructional systems design, intelligence analysis, modeling and simulation, operations research, policy analysis and development, program and budget analysis, risk analysis and management, financial analysis, technical consulting and planning, and transformation and enterprise business strategy.

raw_data.title: Business Analyst I
raw_data.description: Performs functional and technical analysis, assessments, and development tasks. Participates in requirements analyses, data gathering, interviews, and facilitated sessions. Contributes to deliverables. Analyzes user needs to determine functional and cross-functional requirements for IT projects. Performs functional allocation to identify required tasks and their interrelationships. Assists in the development of documentation to reflect the business requirements, including planning documentation as well as testing and training specifications.

raw_data.title: Business Analyst II
raw_data.description: Analyzes user needs to determine functional and cross-functional requirements of IT projects. Manages user requirements and any changes associated with each requirement as the system is developed and implemented. Performs functional allocation to identify required tasks and their interrelationships. Assists in the development of documentation to reflect the business requirements, including planning documentation as well as testing, and training specifications. Supports the Project Manager to communicate and coordinate meetings, presentations, and develop team work products.

raw_data.title: Systems Analyst I
raw_data.description: Maps customer requirements into formal software/system requirements and specifications that are consistent with customer defined business rules. Analyzes system features and functionalities and develops system documentation. Follows change and release management processes. Liaizes with the software development personnel in subsequent phases of the software development life cycle.

raw_data.title: Systems Analyst II
raw_data.description: Collects and writes formal specifications and requirements. Communicates business requirements and needs between development team and client to design and implement business solutions.  Responsible for the collection, analysis and documentation of a client's business needs and requirements.  Use a structured change management process to provide oversight of projects from requirements gathering through completion. Identify, recommend and develop methods, tools and metrics for client business process and operational support. Identify business priorities and advises client on options.  Recommend metrics to ensure customer satisfaction. Develops user help and technical support documentation. Communicates usability issues regarding system interface(s).

raw_data.title: Configuration Management Specialist
raw_data.description: Oversees configuration processes and systems to ensure that all proposed and actual changes to technology and documentation are properly staffed, approved, implemented and tracked.  Documents systems specifications and configuration changes. Facilitates the communication and change management process used for deploying software applications. Must ensure notification of performing organizations or project teams of change activity.

raw_data.title: Business Process Consultant
raw_data.description: Applies process improvement, engineering methodologies and principles to conduct process modernization projects.  Analyzes business procedures for optimization and efficiencies. Provides group facilitation, interviewing, training, and provides additional forms of knowledge transfer.

raw_data.title: Database Developer I
raw_data.description: Designs, develops, and maintains database architecture, data dictionaries, and database schemas. Performs requirements analysis and data modeling using various design tools. Defines strategies for building and populating database structures. Manipulates raw data, the data format, field names, record structure and file structure to achieve database management requirements. Adheres to release management practices and procedures. Evaluates and adapts to new technologies as needed. Interfaces with clients to perform maintenance and testing activities for newly implemented and existing solutions. Develops, implements, and maintains database backup and recovery procedures.

raw_data.title: Database Developer II
raw_data.description: Designs, develops, and maintains database architecture, data dictionaries, and database schemas. Performs requirements analysis and data modeling using various design tools. Defines strategies for building and populating database structures. Manipulates raw data, the data format, field names, record structure and file structure to achieve database management requirements. Adheres to release management practices and procedures. Evaluates and adapts to new technologies as needed. Interfaces with clients to perform maintenance and testing activities for newly implemented and existing solutions. Develops, implements, and maintains database backup and recovery procedures.  Leads team of developers and may direct or lead the entire development effort.

raw_data.title: Application Developer I
raw_data.description: Conducts application development tasks, including coding, configuration, requirement analysis, application design, development, testing, implementation and documentation. Adheres to release management practices and procedures.  Evaluates and adapts to new technologies as needed.

raw_data.title: Application Developer II
raw_data.description: Executes critical components of application development, including coding, configuration, interfacing with client for requirement analysis and application design, development, testing, implementation and documentation. Manages release planning process and follows release management practices and procedures.

raw_data.title: Systems Engineer I
raw_data.description: Executes technical planning, system integration, verification and validation, cost and risk analyses for systems and platforms.  Performance of end-to-end system analysis to include: concept, design, configuration, test, installation, operation, maintenance and disposition.  Ensures the logical and systematic conversion of client or product requirements into end-to-end systems solutions that factor technical, schedule, and cost constraints.  Performs functional analysis. Conducts data center and production environment support and coordination. Provides expertise in one or more engineering disciplines such as application engineering, communications engineering, information engineering, network engineering and security, interoperability analysis, systems standards, military operations, program analysis, requirements analysis, program planning and cost analysis.

raw_data.title: Systems Engineer II
raw_data.description: Plans, analyzes, designs, configures and develops end-to-end systems. Executes technical architecture, system integration, verification and validation, cost and risk analyses for systems and platforms.  Performance of end-to-end system analysis to include: concept, design, configuration, test, installation, operation, maintenance and disposition.  Ensures the logical and systematic conversion of client or product requirements into end-to-end systems solutions that factor technical, schedule, and cost constraints.  Performs functional analysis. Conducts data center infrastructure and production environment support and coordination. Provides expertise in one or more engineering disciplines such as application engineering, communications engineering, information engineering, network engineering and security, interoperability analysis, systems standards, military operations, program analysis, requirements analysis, program planning and cost analysis.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer I
raw_data.description: Collaborates with technical personnel (designers, developers and/or hardware engineers) in the planning, design, configuration, development, validation and utilization for commercial software. Assesses computer provisioning requirements; advises hardware designers of characteristics that affect software systems such as storage capacity, processing speed, memory, firewalls and input/output requirements; designs and develops infrastructures, utility programs, and operating systems. Applies systems and software engineering tools and techniques to develop complete systems level deliverables encompassing multiple applications and processes. Performs individual assignments and work as a member of a project team composed of other analysts and architects. Analyzes systems and technology integration requirements across multiple applications. Communicates and works closely with process and system owners, information technology management, peers, and technical personnel to ensure the relevance of architecture and system designs to business process requirements.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 3 years of experience with Master's Degree

labor_categories.years_experience: 3 years of experience with Master's Degree

raw_data.title: Software Engineer II
raw_data.description: Collaborates with technical personnel (designers, developers and/or hardware engineers) in the planning, design, configuration, development, validation and utilization for commercial software. Assesses computer provisioning requirements; advises hardware designers of characteristics that affect software systems such as storage capacity, processing speed, memory, firewalls and input/output requirements; designs and develops infrastructures, utility programs, and operating systems. Applies systems and software engineering tools and techniques to develop complete systems level deliverables encompassing multiple applications and processes. Performs individual assignments and work as a member of a project team composed of other analysts and architects. Analyzes systems and technology integration requirements across multiple applications. Communicates and works closely with process and system owners, information technology management, peers, and technical personnel to ensure the relevance of architecture and system designs to business process requirements.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 4 years of experience with Master's Degree

labor_categories.years_experience: 4 years of experience with Master's Degree

raw_data.title: Test Engineer
raw_data.description: Designs, develops, and implements testing methods and equipment.  Plans and arranges the labor, schedules, and equipment required for testing and evaluating standard and special devices.  Provides test area with parameters for sample testing and specifies tests to be performed.  Compiles data and defines changes required in testing equipment, testing procedures, or new testing requirements. Provides testing documentation including test plans, scripts, results and analysis. Expertise in working with developers, end users, and organizations to develop test plan, scripts, and scenarios. Coordinate with other teams, test sites to plan and carry out test events to include system, integration, user acceptance, functional, regression testing, automated testing etc. Comprehensive experience in understanding IT products, operating systems, or specialized environment, maintaining evaluating testing process, tracking and reporting issues.

raw_data.title: Functional Area Specialist I
raw_data.description: Analyzes user needs to determine functional and cross-functional requirements.  Performs functional allocation to identify required tasks and their interrelationships.  Identifies resources required for each task. Provides business and analytical expertise in support of a project. Prepares overall design and detailed specifications for system components. Offers knowledge, experience, and insight in a particular area, such as facilitation.

raw_data.title: Functional Area Specialist II
raw_data.description: Provides business and analytical expertise in support of a project. Provides an understanding of the client’s objectives and has extensive knowledge of typical core processes. May prepare overall designs and detailed specifications for system components. Offers knowledge, experience, and insight in a particular area, such as facilitation.

raw_data.title: Functional Area Specialist III
raw_data.description: Provides substantial business and analytical expertise in a specific functional area. Analyses requirements for information systems. May direct the design of adaptations to software.  Offers significant knowledge, experience, and insight in a particular area.

raw_data.title: MasterControl Qx Complete
raw_data.description: MasterControl Qx Complete is an annual Cloud Based Software as a Service (SaaS) license subscription offering of MasterControl's Quality Suite application designed to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of quality and compliance within Government agencies. MasterControl's Qx Complete SaaS solution includes quality management, document control and document management, product lifecycle management, audit management, training management, supplier management, equipment management, deviation management, project management and more. Regulating agencies and Quality Programs derive even greater value by reducing operational cost and minimising risk with a Cloud-based solution. MasterControl’s Qx Complete solution is built on the MasterControl Platform™, which is one integrated platform deployed as a SaaS model with managed resources and upgrades deployed on a quarterly or annual basis determined by the customer. raw_data.title: Program Manager I
raw_data.description: Supervises or directly manages and coordinates several projects within an engagement. Responsible for ensuring project managers deliver timely projects; ensures the quality of work products; maintains financial efficiency; manages client interactions; and conducts project reporting of progress and issues.  Has significant expertise in managing system related projects. Responsible for client liaison.

raw_data.title: Program Manager II
raw_data.description: Expertise in managing and providing leadership to information technology programs that included hardware, software, or services. Manage team of consultants, programmers, developers, and analysts. Experience in managing lifecycle planning and execution, project management methodologies, requirement identification, planning and executing programs budget, schedule, performance progress, and manpower. Manage risks and issues, and ensuring the project is adhering to the IT life cycle process. Manages complex stakeholder communication and expectation across multiple management chains.

raw_data.title: Project Manager I
raw_data.description: Manages and coordinates project through all phases of the systems development/project lifecycle. Responsible for ensuring project delivery within cost and schedule, quality work products, client interactions, issue management and project reporting. Has team leadership experience.

raw_data.title: Project Manager II*
raw_data.description: Directly manages and coordinates several projects through all phases of the systems development/project lifecycle. Responsible for ensuring project delivery within cost and schedule, quality work products, client interactions, issue management and project reporting. Has some expertise in managing systems projects.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert I
raw_data.description: Develops requirements from a project's initiation to its close in the subject matter area for simple to moderately complex systems.  Senior consultant providing analysis, evaluation and recommendations for system improvements, optimization, development, and/or maintenance efforts in the following specialties: information systems architecture, networking; cloud technology, automation; communications protocols, risk management/analysis, software; lifecycle management, software development methodologies, quality management, process modeling and systems security. Provides application, systems, development, configuration, maintenance and data center support.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert II
raw_data.description: Defines the problems and analyzes and develops plans and requirements in the subject matter area for moderately complex to complex systems.  Coordinates and manages the preparation of analysis, evaluations, and recommendations for proper implementation of programs and systems specifications in the following specialties: information systems architecture, networking; cloud technology, automation, communications protocols, risk management/analysis, software, lifecycle management, software development methodologies, quality management, process modeling and security.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert III
raw_data.description: Provides expert  technical, managerial, and administrative direction for problem definition, analysis, requirements, development and implementation for complex to extremely complex systems in the subject matter area.  Makes recommendations and advises on organizational-wide system improvements, optimization or maintenance efforts in the following specialties: information systems architecture; networking; cloud technology; automation; communications protocols; risk management/analysis; software; lifecycle management; software development methodologies; quality management, process modeling and security. Oversees all aspects of projects including day-to-day management of overall contract support operations and necessary support resources.

raw_data.title: Training Specialist I
raw_data.description: Documents and delivers training courses to a wide range of audiences.  Participates in user-support related tasks.

raw_data.title: Training Specialist II
raw_data.description: Designs, develops, documents, and delivers training courses to a wide range of audiences. Provides professional guidance to managers, analysts, specialists, and programmers in the use of the software. Participates in user-support related tasks. Leads efforts in the areas of training plan development, training material preparation, curricula definition and training course delivery.

raw_data.title: Training Development Specialist I
raw_data.description: Responsible for planning, creating, facilitating and coordinating training development and execution of curricula or training plans; supports training testing execution and administration.

raw_data.title: Training Development Specialist II
raw_data.description: Designs, develops, documents, and delivers training courses to a wide range of audiences. Provides professional guidance to training managers, coordinators and specialists. Leads efforts in developing and facilitating training plans, curriculum and training courses, training material preparation and training course delivery.

raw_data.title: Training Program Manager
raw_data.description: Supervises or directly manages and coordinates training development and/or training teams. Responsible for ensuring curriculum developed meets objectives and ensures the quality of work products. Additionally employs learning management methodologies to develop and deploy industry related or customized training. Provides oversight on training development, implementation and delivery; maintains training records; manages trainee interactions; and conducts training reports of progress and issues.

raw_data.title: Training Subject Matter Expert
raw_data.description: Develops training programs, curriculum and/or courses in a specialized subject matter area.  Senior consultant providing analysis, evaluation and recommendations for system improvements, optimization, development, and/or maintenance efforts in the following specialties: information systems architecture, networking; cloud technology, automation; communications protocols, risk management/analysis, software; lifecycle management, software development methodologies, quality management, process modeling and systems security. Provides application, systems, development, configuration, maintenance and data center support.
